Why is my BetterDiscord crashing?
BDFDB is causing crashes following the last discord update. To fix it, remove 0BDFDB.plugin.js from your plugins folder and download it again from the link below, and install it:
https://mwittrien.github.io/downloader/?library

Plugins Folder path:
- Windows: %appdata%/betterdiscord/plugins (Win+R and paste this path in there)
- Mac: ~/Library/Application Support/betterdiscord/plugins
    -you have to do Command + Shift + . to see hidden files (thx ConnieTheTomcat)
- Linux: ~/.config/BetterDiscord/plugins

if downloader broken use this (save ur plugins and or themes just in case) <-----
https://github.com/BetterDiscord/Installer/releases/tag/v1.0.0-hotfix

message.content: Preferences updated: (partial restriction) Kakera rolled from **$mk** can't be sniped for 8 second(s).
This is a premium command! (Player premium and/or Server premium II: <https://www.patreon.com/mudae/membership>)

Use one of the syntaxes below to change the way people can snipe characters on your server (= if players are able to claim the characters rolled by other players or not). Wishseries aren't considered as wishes for this command.

**$togglesnipe 0**: (default value, no restriction) Any character rolled can be sniped by anyone.

**$togglesnipe 1**: (partial restriction) When someone rolls a character they have in their character wishlist, this character can't be sniped for 8 seconds.

**$togglesnipe 2**: (full restriction) Any character rolled can't be sniped for 8 seconds.

**$togglesnipe 3**: (wish restriction 1) When someone rolls a WISHED character, this character can't be sniped for 8 seconds EXCEPT for people wishing for this character (AND the roller)

**$togglesnipe 4**: (wish restriction 2) When someone rolls a WISHED character, this character can't be sniped for 8 seconds EXCEPT for people wishing for this character (the roller CAN'T claim this character either, except if they wished for it)

**$togglesnipe 5**: (combined restriction 1) Any character rolled can't be sniped for 8 second(s) EXCEPT for people wishing for this character (AND the roller)

**$togglesnipe 6**: (combined restriction 2) Any character rolled can't be sniped for 8 second(s) EXCEPT for people wishing for this character (the roller CAN'T claim this wish except if they wished for it)

You can add an option to modify the 8 seconds default value.
Example: **$togglesnipe 1 2.5**
=> Anyone will be able to react after 2.5 seconds.

This command is only available with the server mode 2! ($gamemode)

Digite $ gamemode 2 para acessar o modo 2 ou $ gamemode 1 para voltar ao modo padrão.
As segundas instâncias ($ channelinstance) não podem ser definidas para o modo padrão para servidores regulares.

__Specifities para o modo 2: __

Desative a quantidade máxima de ** caracteres menos populares ** (popularidade por classificação de reivindicação) com este único comando:
** $ limroul 7000 7000 4000 4000 **

=> Este comando significa que você só pode rolar 7.000 $ wa diferentes, 7.000 $ ha diferentes, 4.000 $ wg diferentes e 4.000 $ hg diferentes. Personagens menos populares são desativados.

Você pode ** habilitar ** personagens ou séries específicas com $ antidisable
Você pode ** desabilitar ** séries específicas com $ disable (slots de série ilimitados, mas a mesma quantidade de personagens são habilitados se você for abaixo dos limites mencionados acima)

Apenas Player Premium e kakeraloots / kakeratowers permitem que você use valores mais baixos do que os mencionados acima (desativando assim mais personagens). Observe que você pode apenas usar $ limroul 1 1 1 1 para estar seguro com seus limites mais baixos.

__Server comandos (admin): __
Use ** $ servlimroul ** para alterar os limites para todos. Ele não sobrescreve os comandos pessoais $ limroul. Valores mínimos: ** $ servlimroul 7000 7000 4000 4000 **
$ togglehentai e $ togglehorror fazem parte dos limites de desabilitação, ao contrário de $ serverdisable que permite desabilitar até 750 caracteres adicionais para todo o servidor.

O Modo 2 também tem uma base de 8 rolos por hora.
Modo de jogo $ atual: ** 1 **

Type $gamemode 2 to access the mode 2, or $gamemode 1 to go back to the default mode.
Second instances ($channelinstance) can't be set to the default mode for regular servers.

__Specifities for the mode 2:__

Disable the maximum amount of **less popular characters** (popularity by claim rank) with this single command:
**$limroul 7000 7000 4000 4000**

=> This command means you can only roll 7000 different $wa, 7000 different $ha, 4000 different $wg and 4000 different $hg. Less popular characters are disabled.

You can **enable** specific characters or series with $antidisable
You can **disable** specific series with $disable (unlimited series slots but the same amount of characters are enabled if you go below the limits mentioned above)

Only Player Premium and kakeraloots/kakeratowers let you use lower values than the ones mentioned above (thus disabling more characters). Note that you can just use $limroul 1 1 1 1 to be safe with your lowest limits.

__Server commands (admin):__
Use **$servlimroul** to change the limits for everyone. It doesn't overwrite the personal $limroul commands. Minimum values: **$servlimroul 7000 7000 4000 4000**
$togglehentai and $togglehorror are part of the disable limits, unlike $serverdisable that lets you disable up to 750 additional characters for the whole server.

Mode 2 also has a base of 8 rolls per hour.
Current $gamemode: **1**

Syntax: $channelinstance <instance number>
This will change the instance for **THIS CHANNEL**
If the instance doesn't exist in your server, it will create a new one.

An instance is the same as a new server: use this command to make a fresh start of Mudae on some channels of your server. Your current data will still be available on other channels.

Example: if 10 000 characters are currently claimed in your server and if you use **$channelinstance 2** on this channel, a new instance will be created on your server and any channel where you type **$channelinstance 2** will be considered as a **second** server (with all characters not claimed again)
Your current data will still be accessible on the other channels where the instance wasn't changed.
The default instance is the value **1**.

Note: your server settings will be automatically transferred at the creation of the new instance.
Some commands can be accessed from another instance like that: $mm.2, $pr.2, $im.2, $ima.2, $top.2, $mm serv <server ID>.2

This channel instance: **1**

Syntax: **$haremlimit <value between 15 and 8100>**
This will change the maximum number of characters the users can have in their harem by preventing them to claim if they reached (or are already above) this limit.
Trades and gifts are not affected by the custom limit.

Current value: **8100**

=> Com ** $ shifthour 2 **, sua reinicialização de reivindicação será duas horas mais tarde (= uma hora mais cedo se você reivindicar a cada 3 horas)

Exemplo se a redefinição de sua reivindicação ocorre atualmente às 10:20 => 13:20 => 16:20:

- Com $ shifthour 2 será 12:20 => 15:20 => 18:20

=> With **$shifthour 1**, your claim reset will be one hour later (= two hours sooner if you claim every 3 hours)
=> With **$shifthour 2**, your claim reset will be two hours later (= one hour sooner if you claim every 3 hours)

- With $shifthour 1, it will be 11:20 => 14:20 => 17:20
- With $shifthour 2 it will be 12:20 => 15:20 => 18:20

⚠️ For those who already claimed, these modifications will be applied after their next claim reset.
